  "body": "Hi, I'm struggling to find a way to reduce the consumption of my miner on full archive node. The problem is I don't really know how to do that.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.10.4`\r\nOS & Version:  ubuntu 20.04LTS\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nHaving a node mining on chain but with less cpu consumption.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nAll CPU at 100%. \r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nHere is the flags I used for launching geth : \r\n```\r\ngeth \r\n--http --http.addr \"0.0.0.0\" \r\n--port 30303 --http.port 8534 --http.corsdomain=\"*\" --http.vhosts=\"*\" \r\n--ws --ws.addr \"0.0.0.0\" --ws.port 8534 \r\n--datadir ~/sidechain_data \r\n--networkid 888888888888 \r\n--rpc.allow-unprotected-txs \r\n--syncmode \"full\" --gcmode=archive \r\n--http.api \"debug,eth,net,web3,personal,miner,txpool\" \r\n--ws.api \"debug,eth,net,web3,personal,miner,txpool\" --ws.origins \"*\" \r\n--mine --miner.etherbase 0x0123456789874563215abcdef --miner.threads=4\r\n```\r\nI set 4 threads to the miner but it seems that it's changing.\r\n```\r\nINFO Updated mining threads                   threads=1\r\nINFO Updated mining threads                   threads=8\r\n\r\n```\r\nI have noticed that my node update the amount of thread  it's using is there a way to disable this option ?",
